# .workflows

## Main Workflow: Generate A New Course

This is the most important workflow.

When the user gives this prompt pattern:

```txt
Tạo khóa học "Course Name".

Nội dung lý thuyết gồm:
[content]
```

the AI must follow these steps.

### Step 1: Read Project Instructions

Read:

```txt
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
.spec
.rules
.workflows
```

### Step 2: Understand The Course

Analyze:

- Course name
- Provided theory content
- Natural lesson topics
- Target learners
- Course difficulty

### Step 3: Create Course Slug

Convert course name to lowercase hyphenated English slug.

Examples:

```txt
Agent Engineering -> agent-engineering
Python Cơ Bản -> python-fundamentals
Lập Trình Web -> web-development
```

### Step 4: Create Course Folder

Create:

```txt
courses/<course-slug>/
courses/<course-slug>/lessons/
```

### Step 5: Split Content Into Lessons

Automatically split the provided theory content into logical lessons.

If the user provides enough content, use that content.

If the user only provides a general topic, create at least 5 beginner-friendly lessons.

### Step 6: Create Course Overview Page

Create:

```txt
courses/<course-slug>/index.html
```

The page must include:

- Course title
- Course description
- Target learners
- Learning objectives
- Lesson list
- Start learning button
- Link to homepage
- Link to courses page if available

### Step 7: Create Lesson Pages

Create lesson files such as:

```txt
courses/<course-slug>/lessons/lesson-01.html
courses/<course-slug>/lessons/lesson-02.html
courses/<course-slug>/lessons/lesson-03.html
courses/<course-slug>/lessons/lesson-04.html
courses/<course-slug>/lessons/lesson-05.html
```

Each lesson must include:

```txt
1. Video mô phỏng
2. Tài liệu lý thuyết
3. Ví dụ minh họa
4. Trắc nghiệm bằng JavaScript
5. Câu hỏi tự luận tự ôn tập
6. Đáp án tham khảo
7. Previous / Next navigation
```

### Step 8: Create Sidebar

Each lesson page must include a sidebar/table of contents with links to:

- Course overview
- Lesson 1
- Lesson 2
- Lesson 3
- Lesson 4
- Lesson 5
- More lessons if created

### Step 9: Add Quiz JavaScript

Each lesson must include JavaScript quiz behavior.

The quiz must:

- Allow choosing answers.
- Calculate score.
- Show score.
- Work without backend.
- Work on GitHub Pages.

### Step 10: Add Essay Self-Study

Each lesson must include:

- Essay question
- Textarea
- Button: `Xem đáp án tham khảo`
- Hidden suggested answer
- JavaScript to show the suggested answer

The essay is not graded.

### Step 11: Update Homepage

Modify:

```txt
index.html
```

Add the new course as:

- Course card
- Sidebar item
- Menu item
- Course list item

Preferred course card:

```html
<div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
  <div class="card h-100">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h3 class="card-title">Course Name</h3>
      <p class="card-text">Short course description.</p>
      <a href="courses/course-slug/index.html" class="btn btn-primary">Bắt đầu học</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

If existing homepage style is different, follow the existing style.

### Step 12: Update Courses Page

If this file exists:

```txt
courses.html
```

add the new course there.

If it does not exist, skip this step unless needed.

### Step 13: Check Responsive Layout

Check that pages work on:

- Mobile
- Tablet
- Laptop
- Desktop

Use Bootstrap grid.

### Step 14: Check Links

Check:

- Homepage to course page
- Course page to lessons
- Lesson sidebar links
- Previous/next links
- Back to course link
- Back to homepage link

### Step 15: Final Summary

After completing the task, report:

```txt
Created:
- ...

Modified:
- ...

Added:
- Course overview
- Lesson pages
- Sidebar
- Quiz JavaScript
- Essay self-study
- Homepage course card
```

## Workflow: Create A New Lesson In Existing Course

When the user asks to add a lesson to an existing course:

1. Find the course folder.
2. Create a new lesson file.
3. Add required lesson sections.
4. Update course overview lesson list.
5. Update sidebar in related lesson pages if possible.
6. Update previous/next navigation.
7. Test links.

## Workflow: Improve Existing Course

When the user asks to improve a course:

1. Read the course folder.
2. Identify current structure.
3. Preserve existing content.
4. Improve layout, navigation, quiz, or responsiveness.
5. Do not delete existing lessons unless requested.
6. Summarize changes.

## Workflow: Add Course To Homepage Only

When a course already exists but is missing on homepage:

1. Open `index.html`.
2. Find course section.
3. Add course card.
4. Link to course overview page.
5. Keep existing style.
6. Test the link.

## Workflow: Review Before Commit

Before finishing any implementation:

- Check HTML structure.
- Check relative paths.
- Check Bootstrap layout.
- Check mobile layout.
- Check laptop layout.
- Check quiz button.
- Check essay answer button.
- Check internal links.
- Remove unused code.
- Summarize changed files.
